OrganizationFormalName: National Wildlife Refuge System, Fish and Wildlife Service
MonitoringLocationName: Assabet R at Sudbury Rd upstream of ASR
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Assabet River at Sudbury Rd upstream of refuge. Access is from bridge. Unlikely to be wadeable. Used Van Dorn to collect samples. Take sample on left side of pylon when facing upstream. Because location is on road, recommend collecting water with Van Dorn and then placing into bottles at parking area. Water depth based on first entry from 2017 sampling effort.

OrganizationFormalName: National Wildlife Refuge System, Fish and Wildlife Service
MonitoringLocationName: Winterberry Way at Taylor Bk upstream of spillway
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Winterberry Way at Taylor Bk, upstream of spillway. There is a beaver dam that gets created at the sampling location. Would be good in the future to remove that dam in advance of sampling. Waders needed to access sampling location. Sample should be taken on upstream side of spillway. Water depth based on first entry from 2017 sampling effort.

OrganizationFormalName: National Wildlife Refuge System, Fish and Wildlife Service
MonitoringLocationName: Sudbury R Near Little Farms Rd upstream of GRM
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Sudbury River Near Little Farms Rd, upstream of refuge. Access with waders. Sample taken about 3 m upstream of main riffles directly in line with path down to the water that includes a large rock. See pictures. Water depth based on first entry from 2017 sampling effort.

OrganizationFormalName: National Wildlife Refuge System, Fish and Wildlife Service
MonitoringLocationDescriptionText: Concord River downstream of refuge. Access is via motorboat and sampling takes place from boat. Station is located just downstream of sewage treatment outflow pipe. Pipe sticks out of water at low flows. It is difficult to see at higher flows, but identifiable by a pile of rocks with wire on top of it. Water depth based on first entry from 2017 sampling effort.
